SIMPLE: illuminator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Illuminator
<hw>Il*lu"mi*na`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., an
enlightener, LL. also, an illuminator of books.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One whose occupation is to adorn books, especially manuscripts,
with miniatures, borders, etc. See <er>Illuminate</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>, 3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A condenser or reflector of light in optical
apparatus; also, an illuminant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Illumine</ent>⟦br⟧
